Martin van Cleve. Drunk Peasant being led home, Antwerp, Grisar (Münz, Cat. A44 as P. Brueghel II). Münz, Drawing Cat. A 43, Sale Kende [Galleries, New York] March 1952, N° 438 as P.B.I, given by Münz to P.B.II; [toegevoegde vermelding]: 'F.G. Certainly Marten van Cleve. Figuretype as well as technique speak for M.v.C. cfr. Peasant Brawl by M.v. C. in Brian Koetser Gallery, Oct.-Dec. 1971, N° 50'; Query: Could the Thyssen [onleesbaar] picture and the Seattle fragment also be by M.v.C.?
